 welcome


***************************************************************
1st International Workshop on Cloud Intelligence (Cloud-I 2012)
***************************************************************
In conjunction with VLDB 2012, Istanbul, Turkey, August 31, 2012

http://eric.univ-lyon2.fr/cloud-i/
Contact email: cloud-i@eric.univ-lyon2.fr

*** NEWS ***

Position papers' length as been set to 4 pages.

The best accepted papers will be invited to=20
submit extended versions to a special issue of the Information Systems jour=
nal.

***************
CALL FOR PAPERS
***************

With the increasing success of cloud computing,=20
cloud business intelligence "as a service"=20
offerings have sparkled widely, both from cloud=20
start-ups and major BI industry vendors. Beyond=20
porting BI features into the cloud, which already=20
implies numerous issues (e.g., BigData/NoSQL=20
database modeling and storage, data localization,=20
security and privacy, performance, cost and usage=20
models...), this trend also poses new, broader=20
challenges for making data analytics available to=20
small and middle-size enterprises (SMEs),=20
non-governmental organizations, web communities=20
(e.g., supported by social networks), and even=20
the average citizen; this vision presumably=20
requiring a mixture of both private and open data.

The aim of the Cloud-I workshop is to become an=20
interdisciplinary, regular exchange forum for=20
researchers, industry and practitioners, as well=20
as all potential users of Cloud Intelligence. The=20
submission of research, industrial, position,=20
visionary and student papers are encouraged to fuel up the discussion.

The 1st International Workshop on Cloud=20
Intelligence (Cloud-I 2012) will be collocated=20
with the 38th International Conference on Very Large Databases (VLDB 2012).

The best accepted papers will be invited to=20
submit extended versions to a special issue of the Information Systems jour=
nal.

* Topics of interest

The topics of the Cloud-I workshop include, but=20
are not limited to, the following list.
- Accessibility of Cloud Intelligence
- Analytics for complex data
- Analytics for social networks
- Analytics for temporal, spatial, spatio-temporal and mobile data
- Benchmarking Cloud Intelligence applications
- Cloud data warehouse design and architectures
- Cloud infrastructure for analytics applications
- Cloud Intelligence on linked data
- Collaborative Cloud Intelligence
- Cooperative Cloud Intelligence
- Crowd intelligence
- Data analytics as a service
- Data mining over the cloud
- Economic/payment models for cloud intelligence
- Extracting, Transforming and Loading data over the cloud
- Human-Computer interaction for Cloud Intelligence
- Massive data analytics: algorithms, techniques and systems
- OLAP over the cloud
- Open and private data cross-integration
- Personal intelligence
- Privacy and security in Cloud Intelligence
- Real-time/right-time and event-based analytics, performance issues
- Reliability and fault tolerance in Cloud Intelligence
- Scalability and parallelization for Cloud Intelligence: MapReduce and bey=
ond
- Semantic Web intelligence
- Sharing and reusing Cloud Intelligence results

* Important dates

- Paper submission deadline:                    May 1, 2012
- Notification of acceptance:                   June 5, 2012
- Camera ready paper submission:                June 12, 2012
- Workshop date:                                August 31, 2012

* Submission guidelines

Papers must be submitted electronically as PDF=20
files following the VLDB camera-ready format.
http://www.vldb2012.org/call-for-contributions/preparation-and-formatting-g=
uidelines/

Regular papers and position papers must not to=20
exceed 8 and 4 pages in length, respectively, and=20
must be submitted electronically on the=20
workshop=92s workshop=92s EasyChair website.
http://www.easychair.org/conferences/?conf=3Dcloudi2012

